        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>This is a polarization experiment, so, with the current calibration plan needs to be run as a single SB of at least 3hr duration.

Our target is a pair of galaxies separated by 3-arcsec (so well within the 1/3 primary beam constraint for Cycle 2 polarization studies). Both sources have continuum fluxes of 10mJy in ALMA Band 7, and we expect them to be at least 2% polarized, so the polarized flux of each source will be 0.2mJy (the sources are bright enough to self-calibrate, so we will have no dynamic range problems). We expect both targets to be resolved over about 2 beams, so we aim to detect 100muJy of polarized flux per beam at &gt;5-sigma (Ricean bias means that lower significance detections may be questionable). This gives us a sensitivity requirement of 20muJy/beam, detectable in 2.1hr of integration. The OT adds a further 3hr of calibration (though that may be uncertain, as it seems to be assuming a split into 3 executions, whereas this SB needs to be executed in a single run) resulting in a request of 5.1hr. </prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
